name: Mos Eisley
notes: Mos Eisley was a spaceport on the desert planet of Tatooine, home to various species of aliens from throughout the galaxy.

name: Yoda's Hut
notes: Yoda's Hut was the last residence of Yoda, Grand Master of the Jedi Order, during his years of self-imposed exile on Dagobah.

name: Ewok Village
notes: Bright Tree Village was home to an eponymous tribe of Ewoks on Endor during the Galactic Civil War.

name: Tosche Station
notes: Tosche Station was a power station and repair shop on the outskirts of Anchorhead on the desert world of Tatooine. The Jawa Trader can be found here on the PVE server.

name: Hoth
notes: Hoth was a remote, icy planet that was the sixth planet in the star system of the same name. It notably hosted Echo Base during the Galactic Civil War.

name: Jabba's Palace
notes: Hutt Castle, often simply called Jabba the Hutt's Palace after its owner, was a large sandrock and durasteel complex located at the fringes of the Northern Dune Sea on the planet of Tatooine.

name: Lyss' Museum
notes: Located in the North East sector of the map, showcasing armor sets, ships, decor, and housing options.

name: Jedi Temple
notes: Jedi temples were structures built by the Jedi Order on many worlds across the galaxy to serve as bases of operation for the Order. In them, Force-sensitive individuals could be brought in to be trained in the ways of the Jedi, and The Force.

name: Sith Temple
notes: Sith temples were pyramidal structures built by the Sith on many worlds across the galaxy.
